<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-72-0128 </DOCNO><TEXT>The International Energy Agency, located in Paris, was founded in 1974by the Western industrialized nations. Its main objective was, at first,besides the formulation of energy-political principles, to devise a systemof precautionary measures for the event of a crude oil shortage. Meanwhile,there has been a certain shift in the task of the agency emphasizingmore strongly the analysis and coordination of the member countries'energy policies with a view to medium-term changes in the ratio of energysources.</TEXT></DOC>